        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Surprise! Blasphemous 2: The Third Sin is a new - and free - expansion, and it's out now]]></title>
            <link>https://www.eurogamer.net/blasphemous-2-the-third-sin-expansion</link>
            <guid>1542514</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>
      <article data-ads="true" data-article-type="news" data-article-group="news" data-paywalled="false" data-premium="false" data-sponsored="false" data-type="article">


<header data-component="article-header">
  

    


  <p>

  <figure>
      <picture>
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/unnamed_tfX2g8f.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 1dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/unnamed_tfX2g8f.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.5&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 1.5dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/unnamed_tfX2g8f.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.75&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 1.75dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/unnamed_tfX2g8f.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 2dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/unnamed_tfX2g8f.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=3&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 3dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/unnamed_tfX2g8f.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/unnamed_tfX2g8f.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.5&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1.5dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/unnamed_tfX2g8f.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.75&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1.75dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/unnamed_tfX2g8f.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 2dppx)">
        
      </picture>

        <figcaption>
          <span>Image credit: <cite>The Game Kitchen / Team17</cite></span>
        </figcaption>
  </figure>
  </p>

    

</header>
  <div data-component="article-content">


            <p>Surprise! <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/blasphemous-2">Blasphemous 2</a>: The Third Sin is a new – and free – expansion, and it's out now.</p>
<p>Revealed earlier today, the new expansion "challenges players to explore and overcome a part of Cvstodia that once served as a refuge for the nobles, until The Miracle wrought devastation within the castle walls. The huge, foreboding castle is a quarter of the size of the entire <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/blasphemous">Blasphemous</a> II and Mea Culpa world maps combined".</p>
<figure>
<p>
<a aria-label="Blasphemous 2: The Third Sin Trailer | OUT NOW" data-platform="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/97ydHJeqHi8?autoplay=1" onclick="((e) => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.closest('.video_wrapper').innerHTML = e.currentTarget.querySelector('template').innerHTML; enableElements(); })(event)" title="Click to play video from YouTube">
<span>Blasphemous 2: The Third Sin Trailer | OUT NOW</span>
<template>
<iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/97ydHJeqHi8?autoplay=1" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/97ydHJeqHi8?autoplay=1" title="Blasphemous 2: The Third Sin Trailer | OUT NOW">
</iframe> </template>
</a>
</p>
<figcaption>Blasphemous 2: The Third Sin Trailer | OUT NOW.<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=97ydHJeqHi8" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>The new chapter includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>New map/area to explore (quarter of the size of the entire Blasphemous II map, including Mea Culpa)</li>
<li>One new Boss</li>
<li>New enemies</li>
<li>New weapon – Blade Tipped Whip</li>
<li>New prayers</li>
<li>Unlockable outfits</li>
<li>Boss Gallery</li>
<li>New gameplay experience – three Familars</li>
<li>Six additional music tracks</li>
<li>Five new achievements/trophies</li>
</ul>
<p>Blasphemous 2: The Third Sin is available to download now on Nintendo Switch, PC (Steam, GOG, Epic Games Store), PS5, Xbox Series X/S and Xbox One. The PS4, however, will get it at a "later" and unspecified date.</p>

        </div>

  
      </article>






